caption: Only two kinds of bread, square white and square whole wheat. Should have a hero/sun/hoagie roll. Other than that, great.
Amazing sandwiches and amazing bread!

Bro, I don’t think I’ve ever had a better sandwich. I saw it on Uber Eats and thought, “what the hell; let’s give it a shot. The reviews look good.” I picked it up from the tiny shop outside Waikiki and the smell of bread was delicious. I got my sandwich and ate it at the beach. I got The Machete—turkey, pastrami, ham, salami and cheddar cheese on crack wheat bread. The bread is THICK and fresh. The fillings were also thick. I’m a guy that likes to eat a lot, and for $13.95 this was a deal. I’m so impressed that I will be back and tell all my friends about it. Mahalo.

Absolutely the TASTIEST Sandwiches in the area!  This place takes a simple concept to the next level.  Super FRESH ingredients piled high in-between two slices of fresh baked, delicious bread.  This isn't your routine sandwich experience.  Be prepared to be WOW'ed!  #supportlocal You won't be disappointed!

Excellent bread (their white bread is actually baked with honey), excellent portions for sandwiches, excellent quality.  Be mindful of time though, as they do not keep a ton of supplies on hand, and they may not have the ingredients for your favorite if you come late (though tbh every sandwich I've tried is good so just pick another).

One of my very favorite sandwich shops ever. They actually give you a solid amount of fillings so your sandwich isn't just bread. Not that it would too terrible because their bread is INSANELY DELICIOUS, but still. Great prices too. Love you Machete's!
Fresh ingredients! They make their own bread.  Ordered the Machete sandwich, it was delicious!!!
The Italian sandwich is my favorite with the white bread. Always so good definitely the best sandwiches I have had. Bread is fresh and it always smells so good when you go inside.
Delicious sandwiches with a friendly staff.
Fantastic Sandwich..

This a must eat place while visiting Hawaii! Don’t let the hole in the wall place pass up because it was one of the best sandwiches I have ever eaten. The staff was super friendly and fast! Everybody craves a cold cut after swimming so don’t pass this place up!
Closed on Saturday at 3:45p??? What gives.
Showed up at 2:30pm on Saturday at the Kalakaua location. They said they closed early and I should try the Pizza place next door. WTF??
Baked fresh and generous fillings. Bread very thick so hard to eat a whole sandwich. Lettuce wrap option was appreciated.
Ordered at 4:00pm and they cancelled the order without telling us. I called at 6 pm and they let me know that there werent any drivers available.
Amazing Sandwiches! I've had the turkey ranch and bacon and the machete beyond amazing. The bread is what puts it over the top! Hope one day you'll have tuna on your menu! Always will reccommend you!
This sandwich was AWESOME (machete sandwich from menu) yes it was big but man was it nice, make their own bread an all. Service was great nice chat when waiting. Will give going back!!
One of the best sandwiches I've ever eaten! The homemade bread is so fresh and portions are great. Wish I lived here so I could eat here again. This man knows how to make a proper sandwich.
Awesome sandwiches, very fresh.... I would definitely recommend this place.

Just as I explained with the downtown shop, my worst nightmare came true. They replaced capicola with big HUGE slices of ham. I preferred this place over the DT location, despite their never having White bread in the early afternoon (we order from here 2-3 times a week and I have only gotten white bread a single time; heller? Make more white bread if you run out EVERY day! I hate wheat!). I only dislike one lunch meat and meat period and this is ham. Hate ham. Think it is absolutely disgusting. Despise ham and even on Easter make lamb because I hate ham so much. On top of this, the ham was so horribly fat that it kept stopping me from being able to bite into my sandwich. Foul. I dont care that you're out of something, but if I'm paying for a much more expensive meat and you are out of it, do NOT put mother friggin HAM on my sandwich.
So so so good! And its fast and fair
My girlfriend loves this place and now I've been to both if their location.  It's their bread that sets them apart. If you like thick cut bread you'll want to keep cooking back.
Meannnnnn!!! Super yummy sandwich. I ordered Italian on white and it did not disappoint. Soft bread and fresh meat with veggies. Delicious!!!

This place is not in the tourist trap area. You will have to drive or take a short bus ride to get here. Totally worth it. I went to this place because of the awesome Google reviews it has and I will tell you that the food is 100 percent worth the hype. From the fresh baked bread to the thick and meaty filling it's the best sandwich on the island. I'm sad that I'm only visiting because I would eat here at least once a week. The machete sandwich is so big I had to eat half later. Great food!!! 10 stars
Pretty good sandwich.
Yummy.

The bread is fresh baked and to die for.  Smell of bread baking there is gorgeous. The staff is generous with the filling which is also fresh and great quality.  Best sandwiches in Honolulu.  It's a hole in the wall type of place.  Two tables only in a fairly noisy industrial type setting.  Perfect for takeout or if you just want a quick bite that is delicious and don't mind a bit of noise.  Really reasonable prices too (about $7 to $13).  Parking is tough.
Lots of bread and lettuce, very little meat, one of the most unsatisfying sandwiches I’ve ever eaten, and way overpriced for what you get.
Not joking when they say "mean sandwich". Italian on wheat is my go-to sandwich here. My fiance also loves the pastrami.
Sandwiches are always yummy and fresh but a bit over priced. Some staff are not friendly. This is the Aloha state NOT ...!
Best Sandwiches on island!! But not a lot of workers so delivery wasn't on time at times
Fast delivery and very good sandwiches for a very good price! Happy customer here!
Awesome size bread, meats, and cheese!!

Sandwiches were real good but they were out of capicola...we only found out because we asked if we could have it as a substitute/extra. They told us they've just been using ham as a substitute...the next customer ordered a sandwich that included this and was not informed, which, in my mind is terrible customer service and a lack of transparency. At least inform me and let me decide from there. The bread was amazing, baked right there in front, soft, and thick (I dont care for too much bread but this was airy enough that I did not mind the thickness). Plenty of meats portions, fresh sliced cheese, but very, very simple sandwiches.
We have been on Oahu for just under a year now and as we are ready to  depart from paradise we stumbled onto Machete's. Best sandwiches on island by far and I feel we have been to most!!

My overall experience was amazing. I ordered the Italian sandwich with bacon and avocado spread. The sandwich was excellent melted in my mouth. The size of the sandwich is worth the price. The height of one slice of bread is like about an inch. But the overall sandwich is a little over three inches. The best part of this experience is that my order came 10 mins before the ETA time.
(Translated by Google) Is delicious!  (Original) 美味しいよ！
Amazing sandwiches right by the convention center.
Tasty sandwiches but junk location, no parking, no tables except a couple of tiny tables inside.  Take-out service only.  Limited menu.
Sandwiches are always fresh and delicious service and delivery always prompt pleasant terrific price reasonable always recommend machete mean sandwich a rated 5-star in the buff

Wait what?  You haven't tried the best sandwiches on the Island yet?  They make their own bread from scratch every day and you've never had any that's better.  Fresh, premium meats, freshly sliced veggies and REAL hass avocados.  Family owned and operated, Evan and Rachel take pride in their product, provide excellent service and are the nicest people!  If you're eating during the lunch rush, I recommend calling ahead to place your order.  This place is so popular that sometimes the wait can be 15 - 20 minutes.  But if you call ahead, they will have it ready for you when you get there.
The very best sandwiches at incredible prices and free delivery.
I'm always in the mood for a sandwich. And here the quality and size are amazing. I think the secret is their home made bread. Mmmmm
Great bread but toppings were just ok and service was poor... we were made to feel like we were a giant inconvenience to them so we won’t be back. Plus parking is a hassle.
Fresh baked bread in house, quality ingredients, really good!

Very good non-fancy sandwich place.  Only two bread choices.  That being said there are many menu choices and the portions are very large and reasonably priced.  Convenient walk from the convention center
Some mean sandwiches. A+

If you are near the convention center, don’t waste your time going to Subway. This place blows it out of the water. The fresh baked bread was delicious, and my sandwich was ready before I even finished paying. I had the veggie sandwich. Two thumbs up.
Fresh bread, great quality deli meats, what is not to like?  Do yourself a favour and order the machete, share with a loved one, and go about your merry day.
Really tasty sandwiches
Best sandwiches in Honolulu, the Italian is my favorite! But all of their sandwiches are delicious. Definitely worth the price!
Place is awesome! Has become a daily lunch spot for me. Glad Its so close to my work!

OMG.... The smell of freshly baking bread alone is enough to lure you inside. The staff is super friendly and helpful. The sandwich was made with fresh meats and vegetables. I had mine with avocado spread, and it was so yummy. It's just a simple sandwich, nothing fancy and I think that's what makes it so good.

Their sandwiches are large and in charge! The bread is soft and buttery(but not slathered in butter, not oily,  it's baked in flavor), I would recommend it to friends.  Only downside,  there is only 1 table so you most likely have to do take out.
The bread is great. The service is fast. The sandwich is delicious.
The Italian was near perfection. Combination of capicola and herby vinaigrette made me nostalgic for the old Italian sandwich shops of the rust belt...

My colleague and I went in there during lunch hour to grab sandwiches and were shocked at the speed and quality of them. Got to meet the owner who was working hard in the back and it was over all a great experience. The fresh baked bread was absolutely what made the sandwich. Best sub shop on the island.
They have fresh sandwiches with house made bread!!
Excellent all around.....bread, meat, produce.....all the best!!

This place lives up to the hype it generates. They bake the bread fresh daily which means they might run out. Great high quality classic delicastessen meats and cheeses at a reasonable rate. The location has a small parking lot and isn't great but they informed me that they are willing to come out to your car if need be. I tried the Machete sandwich, a combo of their availbe deli meats and its a half pound of delish. Ask for a side of the dressing, its legit.
So happy this place exists!

The sandwiches are tasty. Went here twice, only thing the amount of meat given is inconsistent. The Machete is plenty of sandwich. Perfect to share for a quick bite. The staff are friendly and the service is quick. They also deliver. Which is a plus since parking in that area kinda lacks.
Amazing sandwiches. The cracked wheat bread is dreamy. So simple but everything is so delicious!
The bread is so yummy. This place hit the spot! Added bacon to our tuna sandwich.
Love this place!
Great sandwiches only problem is the service is lacking . Always has someone training or makes mistakes with the order . But would recommend still
This place is awesome, would recommend
Always good. And delivery on those lazy days.
The Machete sandwich is one of my new favorites. Lots of meat, the way a sandwich should be! Simple sandwiches, but very tasty and very satisfying. And they deliver!

I LOVE LOVE LOVE this place!! Surprised why there are not more reviews. I am a total foodie and this is the best sandwich place so far! The bread is amazing, Every Sandwich I've tried is delicious! Their service is great. And the best part, they deliver! So anytime you're craving one of those sandwiches (and you will crave them) place an order and it'll show up at your doorstep in 20 minutes! Do you guys need a marketing person? Cuz I will definitely tell the whole island and every tourist about it!
Sandwiches so good you are sad when they're gone!

Awesome little sandwich shop with meaty sandwiches. If you love a no-fuss, quick meaty sandwich with homemade bread, then this is the perfect place! They deliver too! I'm going to have my office order for lunch next week!! Mean food!!
Probably the best overall sandwiches on Oahu. Kudos for making their own bread too.
Big sandwich with nice soft bread. Ate half, still full.
The best sandwiches in Hawaii.
It's like the sandwich in cartoons you always wanted to eat,  absolutely amazing.
really good sandwiches at reasonable prices. amazing bread. definitely a new place to try out.
The best sandwiches that you'll have in a while. No doubt.
